Summary: Two opaque spheres flying around one another in a very irregular fashion.
divs: Sighting DetailsMe and my wife were sitting in the parking lot on the east side of saint mary of the woods college waiting for my shift to begin. I was looking at the tree line when i noticed two opaque spheres just above the tree line circling one another top to bottom, during a very fast vertical ascent the two objects then split apart and descended very quickly below the tree line and a second or two later they both shot up in a 45 degree angle extremely fast and they were gone. I could tell they were spheres but they were almost see through with a slightly dark center. I am absolutely sure they were not birds or aircraft.
trends: There have been no other sightings in West Terre Haute
